Higher Education Minister, Blade Nzimande said his department is prioritising safety at campuses. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande said his department is prioritising safety at campuses. Nzimande is also calling on police and communities to also help in keeping women safe. READ: SA calls for state of emergency on femicide "We have been engaging with our institutions of higher learning on the questions of safety," said Nzimande. "There's a task time that was established by Pandor to look at gender-based violence. READ: Students vow UCT shutdown "Security is one of our major considerations, while also not turning campus' into prisons. "We need to stand up and say enough is enough," Nzimande said.